President Donald J. Trump has announced the formation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the EXPO International Fair on "Future Energy" in Kazakhstan. The delegation will be led by Secretary of Energy, Rick Perry, and will include United States Ambassador to Kazakhstan, George Krol, U.S. House Representative Kevin Cramer, President and CEO of the Overseas Private Investment Corporation, Ray W. Washburne, Deputy Assistant to the President and Senior Director for South and Central Asia, Lisa Curtis, and Vice President of General Electric, Ronald J. Pollett.